HJR200 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 HONORING SIGMA GAMMA RHO SORORITY DAY AT THE CAPITOL ON
4 APRIL 2, 2026.
5
6 WHEREAS, Sigma Gamma Rho Sorority, Incorporated, was
7 founded on November 12, 1922, on the campus of Butler
8 University in Indianapolis, Indiana, by seven visionary
9 educators who sought to establish an organization rooted in
10 scholarship, sisterhood, and service; and
11 WHEREAS, Sigma Gamma Rho Sorority, Incorporated, has
12 grown into an international public service organization with
13 chapters across the United States, the Caribbean, Europe,
14 and beyond, impacting countless communities through
15 structured service initiatives and advocacy; and
16 WHEREAS, the sorority's guiding principles of
17 Scholarship, Service, Sisterhood, and Womanhood have shaped
18 generations of women leaders who have excelled in education,
19 public service, business, health care, the arts, government,
20 and civic engagement; and
21 WHEREAS, Sigma Gamma Rho Sorority, Incorporated, has
22 consistently addressed critical social issues through
23 signature programs including, but not limited to, youth
24 development, education advocacy, health equity, economic
25 empowerment, voter engagement, and social justice
26 initiatives; and
27 WHEREAS, chapters within Alabama have demonstrated
28 exceptional commitment to the residents of this state
Page 1

exceptional commitment to the residents of this state
HJR200 Enrolled
29 through mentoring programs, scholarships, community service
30 projects, partnerships with local organizations, and
31 initiatives that promote equity, wellness, and civic
32 responsibility; and
33 WHEREAS, the enduring legacy of Sigma Gamma Rho
34 Sorority, Incorporated, reflects a steadfast dedication to
35 "Greater Service, Greater Progress," uplifting communities
36 and advancing opportunities for individuals and families
37 across this state and the nation; now therefore,
38 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
39 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That on April 2, 2026, we hereby
40 celebrate Sigma Gamma Rho Sorority Day at the Capitol, and
41 we express sincere appreciation for its outstanding
42 contributions, historic legacy, and commitment to the
43 residents of this state through mentoring programs,
44 scholarships, community service projects, partnerships with
45 local organizations, and initiatives that promote equity,
46 wellness, and civic responsibility.
